> **Never auto-launch Hari.** The `fleet-host-agent` file ships in the shared `.cursor/` on **every** VPS (workers included), but it is **inert** — it runs only on an explicit operator request to deploy the fleet board, on the host the operator designates. The per-project workflow below never includes Hari. When a worker run is asked only to "build the backend", do **not** invoke Hari; just have Maya push to the already-running fleet host.

## Workflow

```
Frontend Input → Sunny
  → [Phase -1] resume check: if .sunny/context/state.json exists & != complete →
       resume from the active/first-not-done stage (skip done stages, keep counters)
     else ↓ fresh run
  → context-agent (intake)
  → Architecture:
      architecture-agent → context-agent → architecture-verify-agent
      → [loop if not approved] architecture-fix-agent → context-agent → architecture-verify-agent
  → jhipster-backend-agent
  → context-agent
  → jhipster-verify-agent
  → [loop if issues] issue-resolution-agent → context-agent → jhipster-verify-agent
  → Database:
      database-agent → context-agent → database-verify-agent
      → [loop if not approved] database-fix-agent → context-agent → database-verify-agent
  → Nginx & SSL edge (domain, reverse proxy, Certbot/Let's Encrypt):
      nginx-agent → context-agent → nginx-verify-agent
      → [loop if not approved] nginx-fix-agent → context-agent → nginx-verify-agent
  → Backend testing (generate all 3 layers, then verify/fix each layer in order):
      backend-unit-test-agent → backend-integration-test-agent → backend-functional-test-agent → context-agent
      Unit:        backend-unit-test-verify-agent
                   → [loop if not satisfied] backend-unit-test-fix-agent → context-agent → backend-unit-test-verify-agent
      Integration: backend-integration-test-verify-agent
                   → [loop if not satisfied] backend-integration-test-fix-agent → context-agent → backend-integration-test-verify-agent
      Functional:  backend-functional-test-verify-agent
                   → [loop if not satisfied] backend-functional-test-fix-agent → context-agent → backend-functional-test-verify-agent
  → Frontend testing (generate all 3 layers, then verify/fix each layer in order):
      frontend-unit-test-agent → frontend-integration-test-agent → frontend-functional-test-agent → context-agent
      Unit:        frontend-unit-test-verify-agent
                   → [loop if not satisfied] frontend-unit-test-fix-agent → context-agent → frontend-unit-test-verify-agent
      Integration: frontend-integration-test-verify-agent
                   → [loop if not satisfied] frontend-integration-test-fix-agent → context-agent → frontend-integration-test-verify-agent
      Functional:  frontend-functional-test-verify-agent
                   → [loop if not satisfied] frontend-functional-test-fix-agent → context-agent → frontend-functional-test-verify-agent
  → System integration testing (collective frontend + backend + PostgreSQL):
      system-integration-test-agent → context-agent → system-integration-test-verify-agent
      → [loop if not satisfied] system-integration-test-fix-agent → context-agent → system-integration-test-verify-agent
  → Swagger / OpenAPI docs:
      swagger-agent → context-agent → swagger-verify-agent
      → [loop if not satisfied] swagger-fix-agent → context-agent → swagger-verify-agent
  → Javadoc:
      javadoc-agent → context-agent → javadoc-verify-agent
      → [loop if not satisfied] javadoc-fix-agent → context-agent → javadoc-verify-agent
  → API collection (Postman):
      api-collection-agent → context-agent → api-collection-verify-agent
      → [loop if not satisfied] api-collection-fix-agent → context-agent → api-collection-verify-agent
  → API tests (every endpoint returns correct status):
      api-test-agent → context-agent → api-test-verify-agent
      → [loop if not satisfied] api-test-fix-agent → context-agent → api-test-verify-agent
  → API performance (1/10/20/30 concurrency):
      api-performance-test-agent → context-agent → api-performance-test-verify-agent
      → [loop if not satisfied] api-performance-test-fix-agent → context-agent → api-performance-test-verify-agent
  → Production:
      production-standards-agent → context-agent
      → [loop if blocked] production-fix-agent → context-agent → production-standards-agent
  → Final Approval
```

## Phase 0 — Intake

1. Analyze the frontend: API calls, models, auth, routes, requirements.
2. **Capture the only user inputs at kickoff** (do not ask for secrets, tokens, or `.env` values):
   - **Project domain** — single host: `https://<domain>/` → frontend, `https://<domain>/api` → gateway.
   - **Fleet domain** — global dashboard host (e.g. `fleet.example.com` → `https://fleet.example.com/`).
   - *(optional)* **Certbot email** — if omitted, agents use `admin@<project-domain>`.
   Pass `project.name`, `domain`, `fleetDomain`, and `acmeEmail` (if given) to context-agent. Maya derives everything else: `.env` secrets, `RUN_ID`, `CENTRAL_DASHBOARD_URL`, `CENTRAL_PUSH_TOKEN` (fetched from `GET https://<fleet-domain>/api/fleet-config`), local dashboard URL, early publisher, and fleet pushes.
3. Launch **context-agent** with `sourceAgent: intake`, frontend path, requirements, derived domain model, and the deployment inputs. Maya writes `project-context.md` (Deployment & domain section), initializes `state.json` (with `project`, `workflowStartedAt`, seeded `stages[]`), seeds the dashboard bundle in `.sunny/web/`, and **auto-generates the root `.env` with strong secrets** (PostgreSQL password, JWT base64 secret, registry password) plus `DOMAIN`/`ACME_EMAIL` from intake — no human writes secrets. Maya is idempotent: an existing `.env` is never clobbered; only missing keys/secrets are added. Secret values are never echoed to chat, context, or the dashboard.
4. Confirm `.sunny/context/project-context.md`, `state.json`, `.sunny/web/progress.json`, and the root `.env` (gitignored, secrets generated) exist before proceeding.
5. **Start the early progress publisher** so the run is web-visible from agent #1:
   ```bash
   docker compose -f .sunny/web/docker-compose.yml up -d   # or: PROGRESS_PORT=9090 docker compose -f .sunny/web/docker-compose.yml up -d
   # no-Docker fallback: python -m http.server 8787 --directory .sunny/web
   ```
   Tell the user **all dashboard URLs** for this run:
   - **Local (this VPS):** `http://<server-ip>:8787/agentprogress.html` (open port 8787; plain HTTP until Naveen issues the cert). Auto-refreshes every 5 min.
   - **Local (after Nginx):** `https://<domain>/agentprogress.html`
   - **Fleet (all VPSs):** if `CENTRAL_DASHBOARD_URL` is set, print `https://<central-domain>/` and this run's **`runId`** (from `state.json`) so the user can find this card on the global board.

## Phase 0.5 — Architecture loop

Designs the architecture blueprint + boilerplate before any JHipster generation.

**Exit phrase (must match exactly):** `Architecture approved.`

```
1. Launch architecture-agent with handoff (project-context.md)
2. Launch context-agent to persist architecture-summary.md
repeat:
  3. Launch architecture-verify-agent (readonly) with context handoff
  4. Launch context-agent to persist architecture-verify-report.md
  5. Read state.json — if lastVerdict == exit phrase → break to Phase 1
  6. If architectureVerifyIterations >= maxIterations (5) → cap reached: mark stage needs-attention, surface notifications (local + fleet), continue to next stage (set blocked + stop only if a hard dependency makes continuing impossible)
  7. Launch architecture-fix-agent with the verify findings
  8. Launch context-agent to append architecture-fix-log.md
  9. goto repeat
```

## Phase 1 — Backend generation

1. Launch **jhipster-backend-agent** with handoff from context-agent (include `project-context.md` and the approved `architecture-summary.md` blueprint + draft JDL).
2. Launch **context-agent** to persist `backend-summary.md`.

## Phase 2 — Backend verification loop

**Exit phrase (must match exactly):** `No issues found. Backend approved.`

```
repeat:
  1. Launch jhipster-verify-agent (readonly) with context handoff
  2. Launch context-agent to persist verify-report.md
  3. Read state.json — if lastVerdict == exit phrase → break
  4. If backendVerifyIterations >= maxIterations (5) → cap reached: mark stage needs-attention, surface notifications (local + fleet), continue to next stage (set blocked + stop only if a hard dependency makes continuing impossible)
  5. Launch issue-resolution-agent with verify-report findings
  6. Launch context-agent to append issue-resolution-log.md
  7. goto repeat
```

## Phase 2.5 — Database loop

Hardens and audits the database layer (connections, schema, Liquibase migrations, constraints, indexes, standards, no mock data) after the backend is approved and before testing.

**Exit phrase (must match exactly):** `Database approved.`

```
1. Launch database-agent with handoff (backend-summary.md, project-context.md)
